- Attack vector
- Likelihood (Low/Medium/High)
- Impact (Low/Medium/High)
- Risk rating (Likelihood × Impact)
- Existing mitigations
- Recommended mitigations

## 5. Attack Trees
Provide 2–3 attack trees for the highest-priority threats, showing attacker decision paths.

## 6. Trust Boundaries
Map all trust boundaries in the system and analyze what crosses each boundary.

## 7. Assumptions and Exclusions
Document assumptions made and threats explicitly excluded from scope with rationale.

## 8. Threat Model Maintenance
